.TH "libnvmf_get_discovery_log" 9 "libnvmf_get_discovery_log" "April 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvmf_get_discovery_log \- Fetch the NVMe-oF discovery log page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" libnvmf_get_discovery_log
.BI "(libnvme_ctrl_t ctrl "  ","
.BI "const struct libnvmf_discovery_args *args "  ","
.BI "struct nvmf_discovery_log **logp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
Discovery controller
.IP "args" 12
Optional arguments (pass NULL for defaults)
.IP "logp" 12
On success, set to the allocated log page (caller must \fBfree\fP)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Issues the three-phase Get Log Page protocol against \fIctrl\fP, validates
generation-counter atomicity, and normalises each log entry.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or a negative error code on failure.
